OL,7,F"I shouldn't have left him in the
OL,8,Fgarden, we all know that. I have not
OL,9,Fmet the standard of care. Is it truly
OL,10,Fexceptionally bad neglectful
OL,11,Fbehaviour? No. I messed up, I made a
OL,12,Fmistake."
OL,14,FGiving evidence, Mr Speakman broke
OL,15,Fdown in tears as he recounted the
OL,16,Fincident. He said Albie was dropped
OL,17,Foff by his mum in the morning before
OL,18,Fthey went to drop a woodchip delivery
OL,19,Foff in Burnley.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/11
