OL,7,FAfter they arrived home, the court
OL,8,Fheard Albie followed his dad to the
OL,9,Fback yard, either holding his hand or
OL,10,Fwalking next to him.
OL,12,FMr Speakman then began using the
OL,13,Ftelehandler to move some bags, while
OL,14,FAlbie played, the jury heard.
OL,16,FMr Speakman said: "My intention was to
OL,17,Freverse back and put the woodchip in
OL,18,Fthe bags on the back, but that's when
OL,19,Fhe was there."
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/11
